8 // ----
9 // This file implements the SelectionDAG::LegalizeVectors method. ----
10 // ----
11 // The vector legalizer looks for vector operations which might need to be ----
12 // scalarized and legalizes them. This is a separate step from Legalize because ----
13 // scalarizing can introduce illegal types. For example, suppose we have an ----
14 // ISD::SDIV of type v2i64 on x86-32. The type is legal (for example, addition ----
15 // on a v2i64 is legal), but ISD::SDIV isn't legal, so we have to unroll the ----
16 // operation, which introduces nodes with the illegal type i64 which must be ----
17 // expanded. Similarly, suppose we have an ISD::SRA of type v16i8 on PowerPC; ----
18 // the operation must be unrolled, which introduces nodes with the illegal ----
19 // type i8 which must be promoted. ----
20 // ----
21 // This does not legalize vector manipulations like ISD::BUILD_VECTOR, ----
22 // or operations that happen to take a vector which are custom-lowered; ----
23 // the legalization for such operations never produces nodes ----
24 // with illegal types, so it's okay to put off legalizing them until ----
25 // SelectionDAG::Legalize runs. ----
26 // ----
27 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
28 ----

58 /// For nodes that are of legal width, and that have more than one use, this ----
59 /// map indicates what regularized operand to use. This allows us to avoid ----
60 /// legalizing the same thing more than once. ----
61 SmallDenseMap LegalizedNodes; ----
62 ----
63 /// Adds a node to the translation cache. ----
64 void AddLegalizedOperand(SDValue From, SDValue To) { 0
65 LegalizedNodes.insert(std::make_pair(From, To)); 0
66 // If someone requests legalization of the new node, return itself. ----
67 if (From != To) 0
68 LegalizedNodes.insert(std::make_pair(To, To)); 0
69 } 0

196 ----
197 // The legalize process is inherently a bottom-up recursive process (users ----
198 // legalize their uses before themselves). Given infinite stack space, we ----
199 // could just start legalizing on the root and traverse the whole graph. In ----
200 // practice however, this causes us to run out of stack space on large basic ----
201 // blocks. To avoid this problem, compute an ordering of the nodes where each ----
202 // node is only legalized after all of its operands are legalized. ----
203 DAG.AssignTopologicalOrder(); 0
204 for (SelectionDAG::allnodes_iterator I = DAG.allnodes_begin(), 0
205 E = std::prev(DAG.allnodes_end()); I != std::next(E); ++I) 0
206 LegalizeOp(SDValue(&*I, 0)); 0
207 ----
208 // Finally, it's possible the root changed. Get the new root. ----
209 SDValue OldRoot = DAG.getRoot(); 0
210 assert(LegalizedNodes.count(OldRoot) && "Root didn't get legalized?"); 0
211 DAG.setRoot(LegalizedNodes[OldRoot]); 0
212 ----
213 LegalizedNodes.clear(); 0
214 ----
215 // Remove dead nodes now. ----
216 DAG.RemoveDeadNodes(); 0
217 ----
218 return Changed; 0
219 } ----

221 SDValue VectorLegalizer::TranslateLegalizeResults(SDValue Op, SDNode *Result) { 0
222 assert(Op->getNumValues() == Result->getNumValues() && 0
223 "Unexpected number of results"); ----
224 // Generic legalization: just pass the operand through. ----
225 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Op->getNumValues(); i != e; ++i) 0
226 AddLegalizedOperand(Op.getValue(i), SDValue(Result, i)); 0
227 return SDValue(Result, Op.getResNo()); 0
228 } ----

231 VectorLegalizer::RecursivelyLegalizeResults(SDValue Op, 0
232 MutableArrayRef Results) { ----
233 assert(Results.size() == Op->getNumValues() && 0
234 "Unexpected number of results"); ----
235 // Make sure that the generated code is itself legal. ----
236 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Results.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
237 Results[i] = LegalizeOp(Results[i]); 0
238 AddLegalizedOperand(Op.getValue(i), Results[i]); 0
239 } ----
240 ----
241 return Results[Op.getResNo()]; 0
242 } ----

523 // FIXME: This is very similar to TargetLowering::LowerOperationWrapper. Can we ----

525 bool VectorLegalizer::LowerOperationWrapper(SDNode *Node, 0
526 SmallVectorImpl &Results) { ----
527 SDValue Res = TLI.LowerOperation(SDValue(Node, 0), DAG); 0
528 ----
529 if (!Res.getNode()) 0
530 return false; 0
531 ----
532 if (Res == SDValue(Node, 0)) 0
533 return true; 0
534 ----
535 // If the original node has one result, take the return value from ----
536 // LowerOperation as is. It might not be result number 0. ----
537 if (Node->getNumValues() == 1) { 0
538 Results.push_back(Res); 0
539 return true; 0
540 } ----
541 ----
542 // If the original node has multiple results, then the return node should ----
543 // have the same number of results. ----
544 assert((Node->getNumValues() == Res->getNumValues()) && 0
545 "Lowering returned the wrong number of results!"); ----
546 ----
547 // Places new result values base on N result number. ----
548 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Node->getNumValues(); I != E; ++I) 0
549 Results.push_back(Res.getValue(I)); 0
550 ----
551 return true; 0
552 } ----

554 void VectorLegalizer::Promote(SDNode *Node, SmallVectorImpl &Results) { 0
555 // For a few operations there is a specific concept for promotion based on ----
556 // the operand's type. ----
557 switch (Node->getOpcode()) { 0
558 case ISD::SINT_TO_FP: 0
559 case ISD::UINT_TO_FP: ----
560 case ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP: ----
561 case ISD::STRICT_UINT_TO_FP: ----
562 // "Promote" the operation by extending the operand. ----
563 PromoteINT_TO_FP(Node, Results); 0
564 return; 0
565 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT: 0
566 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT: ----
567 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT: ----
568 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT: ----
569 // Promote the operation by extending the operand. ----
570 PromoteFP_TO_INT(Node, Results); 0
571 return; 0
572 case ISD::FP_ROUND: 0
573 case ISD::FP_EXTEND: ----
574 // These operations are used to do promotion so they can't be promoted ----
575 // themselves. ----
576 llvm_unreachable("Don't know how to promote this operation!"); 0
577 } ----
578 ----
579 // There are currently two cases of vector promotion: ----
580 // 1) Bitcasting a vector of integers to a different type to a vector of the ----
581 // same overall length. For example, x86 promotes ISD::AND v2i32 to v1i64. ----
582 // 2) Extending a vector of floats to a vector of the same number of larger ----
583 // floats. For example, AArch64 promotes ISD::FADD on v4f16 to v4f32. ----
584 assert(Node->getNumValues() == 1 && 0
585 "Can't promote a vector with multiple results!"); ----
586 MVT VT = Node->getSimpleValueType(0); 0
587 MVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToPromoteTo(Node->getOpcode(), VT); 0
588 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
589 SmallVector Operands(Node->getNumOperands()); 0
590 ----
591 for (unsigned j = 0; j != Node->getNumOperands(); ++j) { 0
592 if (Node->getOperand(j).getValueType().isVector()) 0
593 if (Node->getOperand(j) 0
594 .getValueType() 0
595 .getVectorElementType() 0
596 .isFloatingPoint() && 0
597 NVT.isVector() && NVT.getVectorElementType().isFloatingPoint()) 0
598 Operands[j] = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(j)); 0
599 else ----
600 Operands[j] = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(j)); 0
601 else ----
602 Operands[j] = Node->getOperand(j); 0
603 } ----
604 ----
605 SDValue Res = ----
606 DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, Operands, Node->getFlags()); 0
607 ----
608 if ((VT.isFloatingPoint() && NVT.isFloatingPoint()) || 0
609 (VT.isVector() && VT.getVectorElementType().isFloatingPoint() && 0
610 NVT.isVector() && NVT.getVectorElementType().isFloatingPoint())) 0
611 Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_ROUND, dl, VT, Res, 0
612 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, dl, /*isTarget=*/true)); 0
613 else ----
614 Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, VT, Res); 0
615 ----
616 Results.push_back(Res); 0
617 } ----
618 ----
619 void VectorLegalizer::PromoteINT_TO_FP(SDNode *Node, 0
620 SmallVectorImpl &Results) { ----
621 // INT_TO_FP operations may require the input operand be promoted even ----
622 // when the type is otherwise legal. ----
623 bool IsStrict = Node->isStrictFPOpcode(); 0
624 MVT VT = Node->getOperand(IsStrict ? 1 : 0).getSimpleValueType(); 0
625 MVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToPromoteTo(Node->getOpcode(), VT); 0
626 assert(NVT.getVectorNumElements() == VT.getVectorNumElements() && 0
627 "Vectors have different number of elements!"); ----
628 ----
629 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
630 SmallVector Operands(Node->getNumOperands()); 0
631 ----
632 unsigned Opc = (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::UINT_TO_FP || 0
633 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_UINT_TO_FP) 0
634 ? ISD::ZERO_EXTEND 0
635 : ISD::SIGN_EXTEND; 0
636 for (unsigned j = 0; j != Node->getNumOperands(); ++j) { 0
637 if (Node->getOperand(j).getValueType().isVector()) 0
638 Operands[j] = DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(j)); 0
639 else ----
640 Operands[j] = Node->getOperand(j); 0
641 } ----
642 ----
643 if (IsStrict) { 0
644 SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, 0
645 {Node->getValueType(0), MVT::Other}, Operands); 0
646 Results.push_back(Res); 0
647 Results.push_back(Res.getValue(1)); 0
648 return; 0
649 } ----
650 ----
651 SDValue Res = ----
652 DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, Node->getValueType(0), Operands); 0
653 Results.push_back(Res); 0
654 } 0
655 ----
656 // For FP_TO_INT we promote the result type to a vector type with wider ----
657 // elements and then truncate the result. This is different from the default ----
658 // PromoteVector which uses bitcast to promote thus assumning that the ----
659 // promoted vector type has the same overall size. ----
660 void VectorLegalizer::PromoteFP_TO_INT(SDNode *Node, 0
661 SmallVectorImpl &Results) { ----
662 MVT VT = Node->getSimpleValueType(0); 0
663 MVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToPromoteTo(Node->getOpcode(), VT); 0
664 bool IsStrict = Node->isStrictFPOpcode(); 0
665 assert(NVT.getVectorNumElements() == VT.getVectorNumElements() && 0
666 "Vectors have different number of elements!"); ----
667 ----
668 unsigned NewOpc = Node->getOpcode(); 0
669 // Change FP_TO_UINT to FP_TO_SINT if possible. ----
670 // TODO: Should we only do this if FP_TO_UINT itself isn't legal? ----
671 if (NewOpc == ISD::FP_TO_UINT && 0
672 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FP_TO_SINT, NVT)) 0
673 NewOpc = ISD::FP_TO_SINT; 0
674 ----
675 if (NewOpc == ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT && 0
676 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT, NVT)) 0
677 NewOpc = ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT; 0
678 ----
679 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
680 SDValue Promoted, Chain; 0
681 if (IsStrict) { 0
682 Promoted = DAG.getNode(NewOpc, dl, {NVT, MVT::Other}, 0
683 {Node->getOperand(0), Node->getOperand(1)}); 0
684 Chain = Promoted.getValue(1); 0
685 } else ----
686 Promoted = DAG.getNode(NewOpc, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(0)); 0
687 ----
688 // Assert that the converted value fits in the original type. If it doesn't ----
689 // (eg: because the value being converted is too big), then the result of the ----
690 // original operation was undefined anyway, so the assert is still correct. ----
691 if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::FP_TO_UINT || 0
692 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT) 0
693 NewOpc = ISD::AssertZext; 0
694 else ----
695 NewOpc = ISD::AssertSext; 0
696 ----
697 Promoted = DAG.getNode(NewOpc, dl, NVT, Promoted, 0
698 DAG.getValueType(VT.getScalarType())); 0
699 Promoted = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, VT, Promoted); 0
700 Results.push_back(Promoted); 0
701 if (IsStrict) 0
702 Results.push_back(Chain); 0
703 } 0
704 ----
705 std::pair VectorLegalizer::ExpandLoad(SDNode *N) { 0
706 LoadSDNode *LD = cast(N); 0
707 return TLI.scalarizeVectorLoad(LD, DAG); 0
708 } ----

710 SDValue VectorLegalizer::ExpandStore(SDNode *N) { 0
711 StoreSDNode *ST = cast(N); 0
712 SDValue TF = TLI.scalarizeVectorStore(ST, DAG); 0
713 return TF; 0
714 } ----

716 void VectorLegalizer::Expand(SDNode *Node, SmallVectorImpl &Results) { 0
717 switch (Node->getOpcode()) { 0
718 case ISD::LOAD: { 0
719 std::pair Tmp = ExpandLoad(Node); 0
720 Results.push_back(Tmp.first); 0
721 Results.push_back(Tmp.second); 0
722 return; 0
723 } ----
724 case ISD::STORE: 0
725 Results.push_back(ExpandStore(Node)); 0
726 return; 0
727 case ISD::MERGE_VALUES: 0
728 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Node->getNumValues(); i != e; ++i) 0
729 Results.push_back(Node->getOperand(i)); 0
730 return; 0
731 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: 0
732 Results.push_back(ExpandSEXTINREG(Node)); 0
733 return; 0
734 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG: 0
735 Results.push_back(ExpandANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG(Node)); 0

737 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG: 0

740 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG: 0
741 Results.push_back(ExpandZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG(Node)); 0

743 case ISD::BSWAP: 0
744 Results.push_back(ExpandBSWAP(Node)); 0
745 return; 0

747 Results.push_back(TLI.expandVPBSWAP(Node, DAG)); 0
748 return; 0
749 case ISD::VSELECT: 0
750 Results.push_back(ExpandVSELECT(Node)); 0
751 return; 0
752 case ISD::VP_SELECT: 0
753 Results.push_back(ExpandVP_SELECT(Node)); 0
754 return; 0
755 case ISD::VP_SREM: 0
756 case ISD::VP_UREM: ----
757 if (SDValue Expanded = ExpandVP_REM(Node)) { 0
758 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0
759 return; 0
760 } ----
761 break; 0
762 case ISD::SELECT: 0
763 Results.push_back(ExpandSELECT(Node)); 0
764 return; 0
765 case ISD::SELECT_CC: { 0

771 Node->getOperand(1), Node->getOperand(4)); 0
772 Results.push_back(DAG.getSelect(SDLoc(Node), Node->getValueType(0), SetCC, 0
773 Node->getOperand(2), 0
774 Node->getOperand(3))); 0
775 return; 0
776 } ----
777 break; 0
778 } ----
779 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT: 0
780 ExpandFP_TO_UINT(Node, Results); 0
781 return; 0
782 case ISD::UINT_TO_FP: 0
783 ExpandUINT_TO_FLOAT(Node, Results); 0
784 return; 0
785 case ISD::FNEG: 0

787 return; 0
788 case ISD::FSUB: 0
789 ExpandFSUB(Node, Results); 0
790 return; 0
791 case ISD::SETCC: 0
792 case ISD::VP_SETCC: ----
793 ExpandSETCC(Node, Results); 0
794 return; 0
795 case ISD::ABS: 0
796 if (SDValue Expanded = TLI.expandABS(Node, DAG)) { 0
797 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0
798 return; 0
799 } ----
800 break; 0
801 case ISD::ABDS: 0
802 case ISD::ABDU: ----
803 if (SDValue Expanded = TLI.expandABD(Node, DAG)) { 0
804 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0
805 return; 0
806 } ----
807 break; 0
808 case ISD::BITREVERSE: 0
809 ExpandBITREVERSE(Node, Results); 0
810 return; 0
811 case ISD::VP_BITREVERSE: 0
812 if (SDValue Expanded = TLI.expandVPBITREVERSE(Node, DAG)) { 0
813 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0
814 return; 0
815 } ----
816 break; 0
817 case ISD::CTPOP: 0
818 if (SDValue Expanded = TLI.expandCTPOP(Node, DAG)) { 0
819 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0
820 return; 0
821 } ----
822 break; 0
823 case ISD::VP_CTPOP: 0
824 if (SDValue Expanded = TLI.expandVPCTPOP(Node, DAG)) { 0
825 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0
826 return; 0
827 } ----
828 break; 0
829 case ISD::CTLZ: 0
830 case ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF: ----
831 if (SDValue Expanded = TLI.expandCTLZ(Node, DAG)) { 0
832 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0
833 return; 0
834 } ----
835 break; 0
836 case ISD::VP_CTLZ: 0
837 case ISD::VP_CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF: ----

839 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0
840 return; 0
841 } ----
842 break; 0
843 case ISD::CTTZ: 0

846 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0
847 return; 0
848 } ----
849 break; 0
850 case ISD::VP_CTTZ: 0

853 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0

856 break; 0
857 case ISD::FSHL: 0
858 case ISD::VP_FSHL: ----
859 case ISD::FSHR: ----
860 case ISD::VP_FSHR: ----

862 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0

864 } ----
865 break; 0
866 case ISD::ROTL: 0

869 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0
870 return; 0
871 } ----
872 break; 0
873 case ISD::FMINNUM: 0
874 case ISD::FMAXNUM: ----
875 if (SDValue Expanded = TLI.expandFMINNUM_FMAXNUM(Node, DAG)) { 0
876 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0
877 return; 0
878 } ----
879 break; 0
880 case ISD::SMIN: 0
881 case ISD::SMAX: ----
882 case ISD::UMIN: ----
883 case ISD::UMAX: ----

885 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0
886 return; 0
887 } ----
888 break; 0
889 case ISD::UADDO: 0

891 ExpandUADDSUBO(Node, Results); 0

893 case ISD::SADDO: 0
894 case ISD::SSUBO: ----
895 ExpandSADDSUBO(Node, Results); 0
896 return; 0
897 case ISD::UMULO: 0

900 return; 0
901 case ISD::USUBSAT: 0
902 case ISD::SSUBSAT: ----
903 case ISD::UADDSAT: ----

906 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0
907 return; 0
908 } ----
909 break; 0

911 case ISD::SSHLSAT: ----
912 if (SDValue Expanded = TLI.expandShlSat(Node, DAG)) { 0
913 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0
914 return; 0
915 } ----
916 break; 0
917 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT: 0
918 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT: ----
919 // Expand the fpsosisat if it is scalable to prevent it from unrolling below. ----
920 if (Node->getValueType(0).isScalableVector()) { 0
921 if (SDValue Expanded = TLI.expandFP_TO_INT_SAT(Node, DAG)) { 0
922 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0
923 return; 0
924 } ----
925 } ----
926 break; 0
927 case ISD::SMULFIX: 0
928 case ISD::UMULFIX: ----
929 if (SDValue Expanded = TLI.expandFixedPointMul(Node, DAG)) { 0
930 Results.push_back(Expanded); 0
931 return; 0
932 } ----
933 break; 0
934 case ISD::SMULFIXSAT: 0
935 case ISD::UMULFIXSAT: ----
936 // FIXME: We do not expand SMULFIXSAT/UMULFIXSAT here yet, not sure exactly ----
937 // why. Maybe it results in worse codegen compared to the unroll for some ----
938 // targets? This should probably be investigated. And if we still prefer to ----
939 // unroll an explanation could be helpful. ----
940 break; 0
941 case ISD::SDIVFIX: 0

943 ExpandFixedPointDiv(Node, Results); 0
944 return; 0
945 case ISD::SDIVFIXSAT: 0
946 case ISD::UDIVFIXSAT: ----
947 break; 0
948 #define DAG_INSTRUCTION(NAME, NARG, ROUND_MODE, INTRINSIC, DAGN) \ ----
949 case ISD::STRICT_##DAGN: ----
950 #include "llvm/IR/ConstrainedOps.def" ----
951 ExpandStrictFPOp(Node, Results); 0
952 return; 0
953 case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD: 0
954 case ISD::VECREDUCE_MUL: ----
955 case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND: ----
956 case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR: ----
957 case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR: ----
958 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX: ----
959 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN: ----
960 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX: ----
961 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN: ----
962 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FADD: ----
963 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMUL: ----
964 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMAX: ----
965 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMIN: ----
966 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMAXIMUM: ----
967 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMINIMUM: ----
968 Results.push_back(TLI.expandVecReduce(Node, DAG)); 0
969 return; 0
970 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FADD: 0
971 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FMUL: ----
972 Results.push_back(TLI.expandVecReduceSeq(Node, DAG)); 0
973 return; 0
974 case ISD::SREM: 0
975 case ISD::UREM: ----
976 ExpandREM(Node, Results); 0
977 return; 0
978 case ISD::VP_MERGE: 0
979 Results.push_back(ExpandVP_MERGE(Node)); 0
980 return; 0
981 } ----
982 ----
983 SDValue Unrolled = DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node); 0
984 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Unrolled->getNumValues(); I != E; ++I) 0
985 Results.push_back(Unrolled.getValue(I)); 0
986 } ----
987 ----
988 SDValue VectorLegalizer::ExpandSELECT(SDNode *Node) { 0
989 // Lower a select instruction where the condition is a scalar and the ----
990 // operands are vectors. Lower this select to VSELECT and implement it ----
991 // using XOR AND OR. The selector bit is broadcasted. ----
992 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
993 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
994 ----
995 SDValue Mask = Node->getOperand(0); 0
996 SDValue Op1 = Node->getOperand(1); 0
997 SDValue Op2 = Node->getOperand(2); 0
998 ----
999 assert(VT.isVector() && !Mask.getValueType().isVector() 0
1000 && Op1.getValueType() == Op2.getValueType() && "Invalid type"); ----
1001 ----
1002 // If we can't even use the basic vector operations of ----
1003 // AND,OR,XOR, we will have to scalarize the op. ----
1004 // Notice that the operation may be 'promoted' which means that it is ----
1005 // 'bitcasted' to another type which is handled. ----
1006 // Also, we need to be able to construct a splat vector using either ----
1007 // BUILD_VECTOR or SPLAT_VECTOR. ----
1008 // FIXME: Should we also permit fixed-length SPLAT_VECTOR as a fallback to ----
1009 // BUILD_VECTOR? ----
1010 if (TLI.getOperationAction(ISD::AND, VT) == TargetLowering::Expand || 0
1011 TLI.getOperationAction(ISD::XOR, VT) == TargetLowering::Expand || 0
1012 TLI.getOperationAction(ISD::OR, VT) == TargetLowering::Expand || 0
1013 TLI.getOperationAction(VT.isFixedLengthVector() ? ISD::BUILD_VECTOR 0
1014 : ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR, ----
1015 VT) == TargetLowering::Expand) ----
1016 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node); 0
1017 ----
1018 // Generate a mask operand. ----
1019 EVT MaskTy = VT.changeVectorElementTypeToInteger(); 0
1020 ----
1021 // What is the size of each element in the vector mask. ----
1022 EVT BitTy = MaskTy.getScalarType(); 0
1023 ----
1024 Mask = DAG.getSelect(DL, BitTy, Mask, DAG.getAllOnesConstant(DL, BitTy), 0
1025 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, BitTy)); 0
1026 ----
1027 // Broadcast the mask so that the entire vector is all one or all zero. ----
1028 Mask = DAG.getSplat(MaskTy, DL, Mask); 0
1029 ----
1030 // Bitcast the operands to be the same type as the mask. ----
1031 // This is needed when we select between FP types because ----
1032 // the mask is a vector of integers. ----
1033 Op1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MaskTy, Op1); 0
1034 Op2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MaskTy, Op2); 0
1035 ----
1036 SDValue NotMask = DAG.getNOT(DL, Mask, MaskTy); 0
1037 ----
1038 Op1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, MaskTy, Op1, Mask); 0
1039 Op2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, MaskTy, Op2, NotMask); 0
1040 SDValue Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, MaskTy, Op1, Op2); 0
1041 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, Node->getValueType(0), Val); 0
1042 } 0
1043 ----
1044 SDValue VectorLegalizer::ExpandSEXTINREG(SDNode *Node) { 0
1045 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
1046 ----
1047 // Make sure that the SRA and SHL instructions are available. ----
1048 if (TLI.getOperationAction(ISD::SRA, VT) == TargetLowering::Expand || 0
1049 TLI.getOperationAction(ISD::SHL, VT) == TargetLowering::Expand) 0
1050 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node); 0
1051 ----
1052 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1053 EVT OrigTy = cast(Node->getOperand(1))->getVT(); 0
1054 ----
1055 unsigned BW = VT.getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
1056 unsigned OrigBW = OrigTy.getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
1057 SDValue ShiftSz = DAG.getConstant(BW - OrigBW, DL, VT); 0
1058 ----
1059 SDValue Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Node->getOperand(0), ShiftSz); 0
1060 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, DL, VT, Op, ShiftSz); 0
1061 } 0
1062 ----
1063 // Generically expand a vector anyext in register to a shuffle of the relevant ----
1064 // lanes into the appropriate locations, with other lanes left undef. ----
1065 SDValue VectorLegalizer::ExpandANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG(SDNode *Node) { 0
1066 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1067 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
1068 int NumElements = VT.getVectorNumElements(); 0
1069 SDValue Src = Node->getOperand(0); 0
1070 EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType(); 0
1071 int NumSrcElements = SrcVT.getVectorNumElements(); 0
1072 ----
1073 // *_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG SrcVT can be smaller than VT - so insert the vector ----
1074 // into a larger vector type. ----
1075 if (SrcVT.bitsLE(VT)) { 0
1076 assert((VT.getSizeInBits() % SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits()) == 0 && 0
1077 "ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG vector size mismatch"); ----
1078 NumSrcElements = VT.getSizeInBits() / SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
1079 SrcVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), SrcVT.getScalarType(), 0
1080 NumSrcElements); ----
1081 Src = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, SrcVT, DAG.getUNDEF(SrcVT), 0
1082 Src, DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL)); 0
1083 } ----
1084 ----
1085 // Build a base mask of undef shuffles. ----
1086 SmallVector ShuffleMask; 0
1087 ShuffleMask.resize(NumSrcElements, -1); 0
1088 ----
1089 // Place the extended lanes into the correct locations. ----
1090 int ExtLaneScale = NumSrcElements / NumElements; 0
1091 int EndianOffset = DAG.getDataLayout().isBigEndian() ? ExtLaneScale - 1 : 0; 0
1092 for (int i = 0; i < NumElements; ++i) 0
1093 ShuffleMask[i * ExtLaneScale + EndianOffset] = i; 0
1094 ----
1095 return DAG.getNode( 0
1096 ISD::BITCAST, DL, VT, ----
1097 DAG.getVectorShuffle(SrcVT, DL, Src, DAG.getUNDEF(SrcVT), ShuffleMask)); 0
1098 } 0
1099 ----
1100 SDValue VectorLegalizer::ExpandSIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG(SDNode *Node) { 0
1101 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1102 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
1103 SDValue Src = Node->getOperand(0); 0
1104 EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType(); 0
1105 ----
1106 // First build an any-extend node which can be legalized above when we ----
1107 // recurse through it. ----
1108 SDValue Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG, DL, VT, Src); 0
1109 ----
1110 // Now we need sign extend. Do this by shifting the elements. Even if these ----
1111 // aren't legal operations, they have a better chance of being legalized ----
1112 // without full scalarization than the sign extension does. ----
1113 unsigned EltWidth = VT.getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
1114 unsigned SrcEltWidth = SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
1115 SDValue ShiftAmount = DAG.getConstant(EltWidth - SrcEltWidth, DL, VT); 0
1116 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, DL, VT, 0
1117 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Op, ShiftAmount), 0
1118 ShiftAmount); 0
1119 } 0
1120 ----
1121 // Generically expand a vector zext in register to a shuffle of the relevant ----
1122 // lanes into the appropriate locations, a blend of zero into the high bits, ----
1123 // and a bitcast to the wider element type. ----
1124 SDValue VectorLegalizer::ExpandZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG(SDNode *Node) { 0
1125 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1126 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
1127 int NumElements = VT.getVectorNumElements(); 0
1128 SDValue Src = Node->getOperand(0); 0
1129 EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType(); 0
1130 int NumSrcElements = SrcVT.getVectorNumElements(); 0
1131 ----
1132 // *_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG SrcVT can be smaller than VT - so insert the vector ----
1133 // into a larger vector type. ----
1134 if (SrcVT.bitsLE(VT)) { 0
1135 assert((VT.getSizeInBits() % SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits()) == 0 && 0
1136 "ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG vector size mismatch"); ----
1137 NumSrcElements = VT.getSizeInBits() / SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
1138 SrcVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), SrcVT.getScalarType(), 0
1139 NumSrcElements); ----
1140 Src = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, SrcVT, DAG.getUNDEF(SrcVT), 0
1141 Src, DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL)); 0
1142 } ----
1143 ----
1144 // Build up a zero vector to blend into this one. ----
1145 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, SrcVT); 0
1146 ----
1147 // Shuffle the incoming lanes into the correct position, and pull all other ----
1148 // lanes from the zero vector. ----
1149 auto ShuffleMask = llvm::to_vector<16>(llvm::seq(0, NumSrcElements)); 0
1150 ----
1151 int ExtLaneScale = NumSrcElements / NumElements; 0
1152 int EndianOffset = DAG.getDataLayout().isBigEndian() ? ExtLaneScale - 1 : 0; 0
1153 for (int i = 0; i < NumElements; ++i) 0
1154 ShuffleMask[i * ExtLaneScale + EndianOffset] = NumSrcElements + i; 0
1155 ----
1156 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VT, 0
1157 DAG.getVectorShuffle(SrcVT, DL, Zero, Src, ShuffleMask)); 0
1158 } 0
1159 ----
1160 static void createBSWAPShuffleMask(EVT VT, SmallVectorImpl &ShuffleMask) { 0
1161 int ScalarSizeInBytes = VT.getScalarSizeInBits() / 8; 0
1162 for (int I = 0, E = VT.getVectorNumElements(); I != E; ++I) 0
1163 for (int J = ScalarSizeInBytes - 1; J >= 0; --J) 0
1164 ShuffleMask.push_back((I * ScalarSizeInBytes) + J); 0
1165 } 0
1166 ----
1167 SDValue VectorLegalizer::ExpandBSWAP(SDNode *Node) { 0
1168 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
1169 ----
1170 // Scalable vectors can't use shuffle expansion. ----
1171 if (VT.isScalableVector()) 0
1172 return TLI.expandBSWAP(Node, DAG); 0
1173 ----
1174 // Generate a byte wise shuffle mask for the BSWAP. ----
1175 SmallVector ShuffleMask; 0
1176 createBSWAPShuffleMask(VT, ShuffleMask); 0
1177 EVT ByteVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), MVT::i8, ShuffleMask.size()); 0
1178 ----
1179 // Only emit a shuffle if the mask is legal. ----
1180 if (TLI.isShuffleMaskLegal(ShuffleMask, ByteVT)) { 0
1181 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1182 SDValue Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, ByteVT, Node->getOperand(0)); 0
1183 Op = DAG.getVectorShuffle(ByteVT, DL, Op, DAG.getUNDEF(ByteVT), ShuffleMask); 0
1184 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VT, Op); 0
1185 } 0
1186 ----
1187 // If we have the appropriate vector bit operations, it is better to use them ----
1188 // than unrolling and expanding each component. ----
1189 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SHL, VT) && 0
1190 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SRL, VT) && 0
1191 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::AND, VT) && 0
1192 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::OR, VT)) 0
1193 return TLI.expandBSWAP(Node, DAG); 0
1194 ----
1195 // Otherwise unroll. ----
1196 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node); 0
1197 } 0
1198 ----
1199 void VectorLegalizer::ExpandBITREVERSE(SDNode *Node, 0
1200 SmallVectorImpl &Results) { ----
1201 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
1202 ----
1203 // We can't unroll or use shuffles for scalable vectors. ----
1204 if (VT.isScalableVector()) { 0
1205 Results.push_back(TLI.expandBITREVERSE(Node, DAG)); 0
1206 return; 0
1207 } ----
1208 ----
1209 // If we have the scalar operation, it's probably cheaper to unroll it. ----
1210 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::BITREVERSE, VT.getScalarType())) { 0
1211 SDValue Tmp = DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node); 0
1212 Results.push_back(Tmp); 0
1213 return; 0
1214 } ----
1215 ----
1216 // If the vector element width is a whole number of bytes, test if its legal ----
1217 // to BSWAP shuffle the bytes and then perform the BITREVERSE on the byte ----
1218 // vector. This greatly reduces the number of bit shifts necessary. ----
1219 unsigned ScalarSizeInBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
1220 if (ScalarSizeInBits > 8 && (ScalarSizeInBits % 8) == 0) { 0
1221 SmallVector BSWAPMask; 0
1222 createBSWAPShuffleMask(VT, BSWAPMask); 0
1223 ----
1224 EVT ByteVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), MVT::i8, BSWAPMask.size()); 0
1225 if (TLI.isShuffleMaskLegal(BSWAPMask, ByteVT) && 0
1226 (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::BITREVERSE, ByteVT) || 0
1227 (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SHL, ByteVT) && 0
1228 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SRL, ByteVT) && 0
1229 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::AND, ByteVT) && 0
1230 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::OR, ByteVT)))) { 0
1231 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1232 SDValue Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, ByteVT, Node->getOperand(0)); 0
1233 Op = DAG.getVectorShuffle(ByteVT, DL, Op, DAG.getUNDEF(ByteVT), 0
1234 BSWAPMask); ----
1235 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITREVERSE, DL, ByteVT, Op); 0
1236 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VT, Op); 0
1237 Results.push_back(Op); 0
1238 return; 0
1239 } 0
1240 } 0
1241 ----
1242 // If we have the appropriate vector bit operations, it is better to use them ----
1243 // than unrolling and expanding each component. ----
1244 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SHL, VT) && 0
1245 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SRL, VT) && 0
1246 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::AND, VT) && 0
1247 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::OR, VT)) { 0
1248 Results.push_back(TLI.expandBITREVERSE(Node, DAG)); 0
1249 return; 0
1250 } ----
1251 ----
1252 // Otherwise unroll. ----
1253 SDValue Tmp = DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node); 0
1254 Results.push_back(Tmp); 0
1255 } ----
1256 ----
1257 SDValue VectorLegalizer::ExpandVSELECT(SDNode *Node) { 0
1258 // Implement VSELECT in terms of XOR, AND, OR ----
1259 // on platforms which do not support blend natively. ----
1260 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1261 ----
1262 SDValue Mask = Node->getOperand(0); 0
1263 SDValue Op1 = Node->getOperand(1); 0
1264 SDValue Op2 = Node->getOperand(2); 0
1265 ----
1266 EVT VT = Mask.getValueType(); 0
1267 ----
1268 // If we can't even use the basic vector operations of ----
1269 // AND,OR,XOR, we will have to scalarize the op. ----
1270 // Notice that the operation may be 'promoted' which means that it is ----
1271 // 'bitcasted' to another type which is handled. ----
1272 if (TLI.getOperationAction(ISD::AND, VT) == TargetLowering::Expand || 0
1273 TLI.getOperationAction(ISD::XOR, VT) == TargetLowering::Expand || 0
1274 TLI.getOperationAction(ISD::OR, VT) == TargetLowering::Expand) 0
1275 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node); 0
1276 ----
1277 // This operation also isn't safe with AND, OR, XOR when the boolean type is ----
1278 // 0/1 and the select operands aren't also booleans, as we need an all-ones ----
1279 // vector constant to mask with. ----
1280 // FIXME: Sign extend 1 to all ones if that's legal on the target. ----
1281 auto BoolContents = TLI.getBooleanContents(Op1.getValueType()); 0
1282 if (BoolContents != TargetLowering::ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent && 0
1283 !(BoolContents == TargetLowering::ZeroOrOneBooleanContent && 0
1284 Op1.getValueType().getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)) 0
1285 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node); 0
1286 ----
1287 // If the mask and the type are different sizes, unroll the vector op. This ----
1288 // can occur when getSetCCResultType returns something that is different in ----
1289 // size from the operand types. For example, v4i8 = select v4i32, v4i8, v4i8. ----
1290 if (VT.getSizeInBits() != Op1.getValueSizeInBits()) 0
1291 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node); 0
1292 ----
1293 // Bitcast the operands to be the same type as the mask. ----
1294 // This is needed when we select between FP types because ----
1295 // the mask is a vector of integers. ----
1296 Op1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VT, Op1); 0
1297 Op2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VT, Op2); 0
1298 ----
1299 SDValue NotMask = DAG.getNOT(DL, Mask, VT); 0
1300 ----
1301 Op1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, Op1, Mask); 0
1302 Op2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, Op2, NotMask); 0
1303 SDValue Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, Op1, Op2); 0
1304 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, Node->getValueType(0), Val); 0
1305 } 0
1306 ----
1307 SDValue VectorLegalizer::ExpandVP_SELECT(SDNode *Node) { 0
1308 // Implement VP_SELECT in terms of VP_XOR, VP_AND and VP_OR on platforms which ----
1309 // do not support it natively. ----
1310 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1311 ----
1312 SDValue Mask = Node->getOperand(0); 0
1313 SDValue Op1 = Node->getOperand(1); 0
1314 SDValue Op2 = Node->getOperand(2); 0
1315 SDValue EVL = Node->getOperand(3); 0
1316 ----
1317 EVT VT = Mask.getValueType(); 0
1318 ----
1319 // If we can't even use the basic vector operations of ----
1320 // VP_AND,VP_OR,VP_XOR, we will have to scalarize the op. ----
1321 if (TLI.getOperationAction(ISD::VP_AND, VT) == TargetLowering::Expand || 0
1322 TLI.getOperationAction(ISD::VP_XOR, VT) == TargetLowering::Expand || 0
1323 TLI.getOperationAction(ISD::VP_OR, VT) == TargetLowering::Expand) 0
1324 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node); 0
1325 ----
1326 // This operation also isn't safe when the operands aren't also booleans. ----
1327 if (Op1.getValueType().getVectorElementType() != MVT::i1) 0
1328 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node); 0
1329 ----
1330 SDValue Ones = DAG.getAllOnesConstant(DL, VT); 0
1331 SDValue NotMask = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_XOR, DL, VT, Mask, Ones, Ones, EVL); 0
1332 ----
1333 Op1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, DL, VT, Op1, Mask, Ones, EVL); 0
1334 Op2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, DL, VT, Op2, NotMask, Ones, EVL); 0
1335 return DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_OR, DL, VT, Op1, Op2, Ones, EVL); 0
1336 } 0
1337 ----
1338 SDValue VectorLegalizer::ExpandVP_MERGE(SDNode *Node) { 0
1339 // Implement VP_MERGE in terms of VSELECT. Construct a mask where vector ----
1340 // indices less than the EVL/pivot are true. Combine that with the original ----
1341 // mask for a full-length mask. Use a full-length VSELECT to select between ----
1342 // the true and false values. ----
1343 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1344 ----
1345 SDValue Mask = Node->getOperand(0); 0
1346 SDValue Op1 = Node->getOperand(1); 0
1347 SDValue Op2 = Node->getOperand(2); 0
1348 SDValue EVL = Node->getOperand(3); 0
1349 ----
1350 EVT MaskVT = Mask.getValueType(); 0
1351 bool IsFixedLen = MaskVT.isFixedLengthVector(); 0
1352 ----
1353 EVT EVLVecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), EVL.getValueType(), 0
1354 MaskVT.getVectorElementCount()); ----
1355 ----
1356 // If we can't construct the EVL mask efficiently, it's better to unroll. ----
1357 if ((IsFixedLen && 0
1358 !TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::BUILD_VECTOR, EVLVecVT)) || 0
1359 (!IsFixedLen && 0
1360 (!TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::STEP_VECTOR, EVLVecVT) || 0
1361 !TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR, EVLVecVT)))) 0
1362 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node); 0
1363 ----
1364 // If using a SETCC would result in a different type than the mask type, ----
1365 // unroll. ----
1366 if (TLI.getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), 0
1367 EVLVecVT) != MaskVT) 0
1368 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node); 0
1369 ----
1370 SDValue StepVec = DAG.getStepVector(DL, EVLVecVT); 0
1371 SDValue SplatEVL = DAG.getSplat(EVLVecVT, DL, EVL); 0
1372 SDValue EVLMask = ----
1373 DAG.getSetCC(DL, MaskVT, StepVec, SplatEVL, ISD::CondCode::SETULT); 0
1374 ----
1375 SDValue FullMask = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, MaskVT, Mask, EVLMask); 0
1376 return DAG.getSelect(DL, Node->getValueType(0), FullMask, Op1, Op2); 0
1377 } 0
1378 ----
1379 SDValue VectorLegalizer::ExpandVP_REM(SDNode *Node) { 0
1380 // Implement VP_SREM/UREM in terms of VP_SDIV/VP_UDIV, VP_MUL, VP_SUB. ----
1381 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
1382 ----
1383 unsigned DivOpc = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::VP_SREM ? ISD::VP_SDIV : ISD::VP_UDIV; 0
1384 ----
1385 if (!TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(DivOpc, VT) || 0
1386 !TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::VP_MUL, VT) || 0
1387 !TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::VP_SUB, VT)) 0
1388 return SDValue(); 0
1389 ----
1390 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1391 ----
1392 SDValue Dividend = Node->getOperand(0); 0
1393 SDValue Divisor = Node->getOperand(1); 0
1394 SDValue Mask = Node->getOperand(2); 0
1395 SDValue EVL = Node->getOperand(3); 0
1396 ----
1397 // X % Y -> X-X/Y*Y ----
1398 SDValue Div = DAG.getNode(DivOpc, DL, VT, Dividend, Divisor, Mask, EVL); 0
1399 SDValue Mul = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_MUL, DL, VT, Divisor, Div, Mask, EVL); 0
1400 return DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SUB, DL, VT, Dividend, Mul, Mask, EVL); 0
1401 } 0
1402 ----
1403 void VectorLegalizer::ExpandFP_TO_UINT(SDNode *Node, 0
1404 SmallVectorImpl &Results) { ----
1405 // Attempt to expand using TargetLowering. ----
1406 SDValue Result, Chain; 0
1407 if (TLI.expandFP_TO_UINT(Node, Result, Chain, DAG)) { 0
1408 Results.push_back(Result); 0
1409 if (Node->isStrictFPOpcode()) 0
1410 Results.push_back(Chain); 0
1411 return; 0
1412 } ----
1413 ----
1414 // Otherwise go ahead and unroll. ----
1415 if (Node->isStrictFPOpcode()) { 0
1416 UnrollStrictFPOp(Node, Results); 0
1417 return; 0
1418 } ----
1419 ----
1420 Results.push_back(DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node)); 0
1421 } ----
1422 ----
1423 void VectorLegalizer::ExpandUINT_TO_FLOAT(SDNode *Node, 0
1424 SmallVectorImpl &Results) { ----
1425 bool IsStrict = Node->isStrictFPOpcode(); 0
1426 unsigned OpNo = IsStrict ? 1 : 0; 0
1427 SDValue Src = Node->getOperand(OpNo); 0
1428 EVT VT = Src.getValueType(); 0
1429 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1430 ----
1431 // Attempt to expand using TargetLowering. ----
1432 SDValue Result; 0
1433 SDValue Chain; 0
1434 if (TLI.expandUINT_TO_FP(Node, Result, Chain, DAG)) { 0
1435 Results.push_back(Result); 0
1436 if (IsStrict) 0
1437 Results.push_back(Chain); 0
1438 return; 0
1439 } ----
1440 ----
1441 // Make sure that the SINT_TO_FP and SRL instructions are available. ----
1442 if (((!IsStrict && TLI.getOperationAction(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, VT) == 0
1443 TargetLowering::Expand) || 0
1444 (IsStrict && TLI.getOperationAction(ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP, VT) == 0
1445 TargetLowering::Expand)) || 0
1446 TLI.getOperationAction(ISD::SRL, VT) == TargetLowering::Expand) { 0
1447 if (IsStrict) { 0
1448 UnrollStrictFPOp(Node, Results); 0
1449 return; 0
1450 } ----
1451 ----
1452 Results.push_back(DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node)); 0
1453 return; 0
1454 } ----
1455 ----
1456 unsigned BW = VT.getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
1457 assert((BW == 64 || BW == 32) && 0
1458 "Elements in vector-UINT_TO_FP must be 32 or 64 bits wide"); ----
1459 ----
1460 SDValue HalfWord = DAG.getConstant(BW / 2, DL, VT); 0
1461 ----
1462 // Constants to clear the upper part of the word. ----
1463 // Notice that we can also use SHL+SHR, but using a constant is slightly ----
1464 // faster on x86. ----
1465 uint64_t HWMask = (BW == 64) ? 0x00000000FFFFFFFF : 0x0000FFFF; 0
1466 SDValue HalfWordMask = DAG.getConstant(HWMask, DL, VT); 0
1467 ----
1468 // Two to the power of half-word-size. ----
1469 SDValue TWOHW = ----
1470 DAG.getConstantFP(1ULL << (BW / 2), DL, Node->getValueType(0)); 0
1471 ----
1472 // Clear upper part of LO, lower HI ----
1473 SDValue HI = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, Src, HalfWord); 0
1474 SDValue LO = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, Src, HalfWordMask); 0
1475 ----
1476 if (IsStrict) { 0
1477 // Convert hi and lo to floats ----
1478 // Convert the hi part back to the upper values ----
1479 // TODO: Can any fast-math-flags be set on these nodes? ----
1480 SDValue fHI = DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP, DL, 0
1481 {Node->getValueType(0), MVT::Other}, 0
1482 {Node->getOperand(0), HI}); 0
1483 fHI = DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_FMUL, DL, {Node->getValueType(0), MVT::Other}, 0
1484 {fHI.getValue(1), fHI, TWOHW}); 0
1485 SDValue fLO = DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP, DL, 0
1486 {Node->getValueType(0), MVT::Other}, 0
1487 {Node->getOperand(0), LO}); 0
1488 ----
1489 SDValue TF = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, fHI.getValue(1), 0
1490 fLO.getValue(1)); ----
1491 ----
1492 // Add the two halves ----
1493 SDValue Result = ----
1494 DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_FADD, DL, {Node->getValueType(0), MVT::Other}, 0
1495 {TF, fHI, fLO}); ----
1496 ----
1497 Results.push_back(Result); 0
1498 Results.push_back(Result.getValue(1)); 0
1499 return; 0
1500 } ----
1501 ----
1502 // Convert hi and lo to floats ----
1503 // Convert the hi part back to the upper values ----
1504 // TODO: Can any fast-math-flags be set on these nodes? ----
1505 SDValue fHI = DAG.getNode(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, DL, Node->getValueType(0), HI); 0
1506 fHI = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMUL, DL, Node->getValueType(0), fHI, TWOHW); 0
1507 SDValue fLO = DAG.getNode(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, DL, Node->getValueType(0), LO); 0
1508 ----
1509 // Add the two halves ----
1510 Results.push_back( 0
1511 DAG.getNode(ISD::FADD, DL, Node->getValueType(0), fHI, fLO)); 0
1512 } 0
1513 ----
1514 SDValue VectorLegalizer::ExpandFNEG(SDNode *Node) { 0
1515 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FSUB, Node->getValueType(0))) { 0
1516 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1517 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstantFP(-0.0, DL, Node->getValueType(0)); 0
1518 // TODO: If FNEG had fast-math-flags, they'd get propagated to this FSUB. ----
1519 return DAG.getNode(ISD::FSUB, DL, Node->getValueType(0), Zero, 0
1520 Node->getOperand(0)); 0
1521 } 0
1522 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node); 0
1523 } ----
1524 ----
1525 void VectorLegalizer::ExpandFSUB(SDNode *Node, 0
1526 SmallVectorImpl &Results) { ----
1527 // For floating-point values, (a-b) is the same as a+(-b). If FNEG is legal, ----
1528 // we can defer this to operation legalization where it will be lowered as ----
1529 // a+(-b). ----
1530 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
1531 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FNEG, VT) && 0
1532 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FADD, VT)) 0
1533 return; // Defer to LegalizeDAG 0
1534 ----
1535 SDValue Tmp = DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node); 0
1536 Results.push_back(Tmp); 0
1537 } ----
1538 ----
1539 void VectorLegalizer::ExpandSETCC(SDNode *Node, 0
1540 SmallVectorImpl &Results) { ----
1541 bool NeedInvert = false; 0
1542 bool IsVP = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::VP_SETCC; 0
1543 bool IsStrict = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_FSETCC || 0
1544 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS; 0
1545 bool IsSignaling = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS; 0
1546 unsigned Offset = IsStrict ? 1 : 0; 0
1547 ----
1548 SDValue Chain = IsStrict ? Node->getOperand(0) : SDValue(); 0
1549 SDValue LHS = Node->getOperand(0 + Offset); 0
1550 SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(1 + Offset); 0
1551 SDValue CC = Node->getOperand(2 + Offset); 0
1552 ----
1553 MVT OpVT = LHS.getSimpleValueType(); 0
1554 ISD::CondCode CCCode = cast(CC)->get(); 0
1555 ----
1556 if (TLI.getCondCodeAction(CCCode, OpVT) != TargetLowering::Expand) { 0
1557 if (IsStrict) { 0
1558 UnrollStrictFPOp(Node, Results); 0
1559 return; 0
1560 } ----
1561 Results.push_back(UnrollVSETCC(Node)); 0
1562 return; 0
1563 } ----
1564 ----
1565 SDValue Mask, EVL; 0
1566 if (IsVP) { 0
1567 Mask = Node->getOperand(3 + Offset); 0
1568 EVL = Node->getOperand(4 + Offset); 0
1569 } ----
1570 ----
1571 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
1572 bool Legalized = ----
1573 TLI.LegalizeSetCCCondCode(DAG, Node->getValueType(0), LHS, RHS, CC, Mask, 0
1574 EVL, NeedInvert, dl, Chain, IsSignaling); ----
1575 ----
1576 if (Legalized) { 0
1577 // If we expanded the SETCC by swapping LHS and RHS, or by inverting the ----
1578 // condition code, create a new SETCC node. ----
1579 if (CC.getNode()) { 0
1580 if (IsStrict) { 0
1581 LHS = DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, Node->getVTList(), 0
1582 {Chain, LHS, RHS, CC}, Node->getFlags()); ----
1583 Chain = LHS.getValue(1); 0
1584 } else if (IsVP) { 0
1585 LHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SETCC, dl, Node->getValueType(0), 0
1586 {LHS, RHS, CC, Mask, EVL}, Node->getFlags()); ----
1587 } else { ----
1588 LHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCC, dl, Node->getValueType(0), LHS, RHS, CC, 0
1589 Node->getFlags()); ----
1590 } ----
1591 } ----
1592 ----
1593 // If we expanded the SETCC by inverting the condition code, then wrap ----
1594 // the existing SETCC in a NOT to restore the intended condition. ----
